{
  "texts": [
    "Following the initial generation of faulty code by the LLM, this mechanism invites testers to engage directly with the output, providing feedback on the accuracy, relevance, and overall quality of the simulated faults.",
    "This feedback is then fed back into the LLM for code refinement.",
    "The RLHF Mechanism embodies the methodology's adaptive spirit, ensuring that the solution remains responsive to the needs of testers and the demands of the ever-evolving software landscape.4) Automated Integration and Testing Tool: Completing the cycle is the Automated Integration and Testing Tool, which ensures the smooth transition of generated faults from concept to application.",
    "The tool automates the process of integrating the LLM-generated faulty code into the target software's codebase, meticulously placing each fault in its designated context for maximum impact during testing.",
    "Beyond integration, the tool facilitates a comprehensive suite of tests designed to activate the faults and observe the software's response, providing testers with invaluable insights into the system's resilience and areas for improvement.IV."
  ]
}